        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="48" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Council/8–3145</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Director of the Office of
                        Far Eastern Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Ballantine</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-31">August 31,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Chen<note n="23" xml:id="d48fn23">Chen Chih-mai, Counselor of the Chinese
                        Embassy.</note> said that the other day he had been informed by Mr.
                        Vincent<note n="24" xml:id="d48fn24">John Carter Vincent, Chief of the
                        Division of Chinese Affairs.</note> that the United States Government did
                    not intend to raise any Far Eastern questions at the Council of Foreign
                    Ministers in London. He said that he had been instructed by his Government to
                    inform the Department that the Chinese Government likewise did not intend to
                    raise any Far Eastern questions there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J[<hi rend="smallcaps">oseph</hi>] W. B[<hi rend="smallcaps">allantine</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
